DIMON, Respondent, v. KEERY, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. January 12, 1894.) Action by Charles L. Dimon, as administrator, against Martha Keery.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and PARKER, JJ.

T. H. Friend, for appellant. W. R. Wilder, for respondent.

No opinion. Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
